HEADWORD: Nixie
<hw>Nix"ie</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>See
<er>Nix</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Nothing.</def> <mark>[Slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(U. S. Mail Service)</fld> <def>A piece of mail
matter which cannot be delivered, either because no post office exists
at the place to which is it addressed, or because there is no place of
the name mentioned in the designated State, Territory, or the
like.</def> <mark>[Cant]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nixie clerk</ent>⟦br⟧
